# Backend Structure

The backend is an Express.js application with MongoDB as the database.

## Core Files
- [backend/server.js](mdc:backend/server.js) - Server entry point and configuration
- [backend/seed.js](mdc:backend/seed.js) - Database seed utility

## Directory Structure
- `routes/` - API route definitions
- `controllers/` - Request handlers that process route requests
- `models/` - MongoDB schema definitions
- `middleware/` - Express middleware functions
- `services/` - Business logic and service functions
- `utils/` - Utility functions
- `src/` - Additional source code

## API Routes
The backend exposes the following API routes:
- `/api/auth` - Authentication endpoints
- `/api/users` - User management
- `/api/activity-log` - Activity logging
- `/api/items` - Item management
- `/api/vendors` - Vendor management
- `/api/brokers` - Broker management
- `/api/customers` - Customer management
- `/api/commissioners` - Commissioner management
- `/api/vendor-invoices` - Vendor invoice management

## Development
- Start the backend server with `npm start` or `node server.js`
